Algorithm: vigilantsolutions_008 | Submission Date: 2020_08_03 | Report Card Last Updated: 2020-08-06







Operating on visa images, the heatmap shows false match observed over impostor comparisons of faces from different individuals who have the given age pair. False matches are counted against a recognition threshold fixed globally to give FMR = 0.0001 over all on the order of 1010 impostor comparisons. The text in each box gives the same quantity as that coded by the color. Light colors present a security vulnerability to, for example, a passport gate.
